SIMPLE: sunsetting
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sunsetting
<hw>Sun"set`ting</hw>, }</mhw>
<pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The descent of the sun below the horizon;
also, the time when the sun sets; evening. Also used
figuratively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>'T is the <qex>sunset</qex> of life gives me mystical lore.</q>
<rj><qau>Campbell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, the region where the sun sets; the
west.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sunset shell</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a West
Indian marine bivalve (<spn>Tellina radiata</spn>) having a smooth shell
marked with radiating bands of varied colors resembling those seen at
sunset or before sunrise; -- called also <altname>rising
sun</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sunshade</ent>⟦br⟧
